Innovation Talks. Erich Clementi | BBS

























 









 

















DESCRIPTION
REGISTRATION







Innovation Talks. Erich Clementi

                                            December 13,  2016                  
- 6.00 PM - Bologna Business School - Villa Guastavillani - Via degli Scalini, 18 - Bologna


The fourth Keynote Speaker of the fall edition is Erich Clementi, is Senior Vice President, IBM Sales & Distribution with a focus on Europe, North America and IBM industry sector teams globally.

The event, organized in collaboration with Philip Morris Italia, will address the theme of Industry 4.0.
Erich Clementi has graduated in business administration at the Leopold-Franzens University in Innsbruck, Austria. In 1984 he joined the IBM world, started working in the Milan headquarters and in the 90s he began directing the operations of sales & marketing for bank and financial accounts throughout Europe.
From 1999 to 2003, he held various leadership roles in business strategy, marketing and sales. With this latest role he has followed the sales in Europe, Middle East and Africa, and has also handled the marketing of the entire range of IBM hardware, including IBM server computers and printers, storage devices, network components and microelectronic products .
He has also led the Business Systems Division in IBM Systems and Technology Group, as well as IBM’s Global Process Services unit, which became one of the fastest growing businesses of IBM to fill the role he has now.
 

To participate register here.
The event will be held in Italian with simultaneous translation into English.





 






 
 



