Full biography
			
			
			
			Erich Clementi is Senior Vice President, Global Markets and Chairman, IBM Europe for the IBM Corporation with a focus on Europe, North America and IBM industry sector teams globally.

Prior to this position, Erich led IBM Global Technology Services, where he held worldwide responsibility for cloud computing services, IT and business process outsourcing, project-based services, and technical support services. 
In recent years, Erich ran IBM’s strategy function responsible for identifying and executing on major growth opportunities including cloud computing. He has also led the Business Systems Division in IBM Systems and Technology Group, as well as IBM’s Global Process Services unit, and IBM’s System z business.
He joined IBM in Milan in 1984, and holds a degree in business administration from the Leopold-Franzens University in Innsbruck, Austria.










